@elodiegif @KnightCenterUT @ICFJ @TheCAOV @pmayorga_o @YemileBucay @Rosental @AliBaskerville Know your enemy. Do risk assessments and critical analysis. @elodievialle 

Strengthen awareness of ourselves and leave aside competition within the profession, because it prevents connections. @pmayorga_o

Make friends &amp; allies on assignments. Keep each other safe. @YemileBucay

@elodiegif @KnightCenterUT @ICFJ @TheCAOV @pmayorga_o @YemileBucay What can journalism schools do?

They can be proactive in making sure they don't let students graduate without knowing about safety issues in journalism, #onlineviolence and mental health. 
-@Rosental

@elodiegif @KnightCenterUT @ICFJ @TheCAOV @pmayorga_o "One of the key things that has been missing is centering identity when we discuss risk.

Sexual violence is not the only form of gender-based violence and sexual violence doesn't only affect women. Identity is a starting point. We need to treat risk holistically."

-@YemileBucay

@elodiegif @KnightCenterUT @ICFJ @TheCAOV "Sometimes we're presented as war correspondents, but a war correspondents get ready... the war came to us.

Reporting affects your mind, body and emotions. You're a human, not a robot."

- @pmayorga_o on reporting in Latin America

@elodiegif @KnightCenterUT "For women to feel safe in this profession, do they need to suffer? Why is it not up to the environment to change?

'MaMa Project' opens up the closet where all of these issues have been covered up &amp; says we need to speak about this in newsrooms."

-Tatiana Mossot, founder

